<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">711.932/7–2048: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-20T19:00:00-04:00">July 20, 1948—7
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1053. Embtel 1320, July 20, Emb requested urge Chinese Govt seek immediately
                        legislative approval Senate reservation FCN treaty. Dept exploring possible
                        means for obtaining, either before or after exchange ratifications,
                        objectives sought in proposed exchanges notes. Views Emb requested.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>